description: Nearly 70% of the weapons surrendered in Manipur came from four Valley districts — Imphal East, Imphal West, Thoubal, and Bishnupur. These surrenders followed a call given by governor Ajay Bhalla. A total of 991 weapons, along with thousands of ammunition items, grenades, bombs, and IEDs, were turned in by rebels and protesters.
title: 70% of Manipur weapons surrendered after guv call came from 4 valley districts

description: Opposition parties Congress and CPM expressed national security concerns over the recent partnerships between Airtel, Jio, and Starlink. Congress alleged that PM Modi orchestrated these deals to gain favor with US President Trump via Starlink owner Elon Musk. They questioned the implications for national security and the method of spectrum allocation, emphasizing the critical nature of telecom services for defense.
title: Cong, CPM question Starlink deal, raise national security fears

description: A draft referendum ballot has been proposed by the Kuki-Zo tribe in Manipur to decide on creating a Union Territory from Manipur’s hill districts, directly governed by the Centre. The Kuki-Zo Council has withdrawn an indefinite shutdown following a youth's death in a clash with security forces.
title: Kuki referendum draft eyes state split
March 15 exam ‘mixup’: CBSE offers 2nd shot

description: In the past five years, only 1,525 driving licenses were cancelled for traffic violations nationwide, with Tamil Nadu accounting for half of these. This low number contrasts sharply with a mere handful of cancellations in states like Delhi, Bengal, Haryana, and Maharashtra. Road transport minister Nitin Gadkari highlighted these figures, indicating that challenges remain in digital enforcement.
title: Only 1,525 DLs cancelled in 5 years despite digital efforts to curb violations

description: India has identified 388 illegal Indian immigrants in the US since President Trump's deportation campaign. These individuals have been verified and returned to India, mainly through aid from the International Organisation for Migration. There's ongoing verification of more nationals. Authorities emphasize the need to crack down on the illegal migration industry and prosecute agents involved.
title: Only 388 Indian illegals in US verified, all back in India: Govt

description: Puducherry will implement a three-language policy, allowing students to choose a third language, which can be a regional language instead of Hindi. Minister A Namassivayam refuted allegations of Hindi imposition. Opposing parties condemned the decision. Schools in Puducherry recently switched to CBSE, while those in Mahe and Yanam follow Kerala and Andhra boards respectively.
title: Puducherry to adopt 3-language policy, mantri says Cong imposed Hindi on TN

description: Tamil Nadu's Stalin government replaced the rupee symbol with a Tamil letter for the state budget, sparking criticism from Union Finance Minister Nirmala Sitharaman and BJP leaders. They argue that the rupee symbol has national significance and should not be altered. The DMK defends the move as a promotion of regional pride.
title: Stalin govt's budget logo swaps ₹ with Tamil letter

description: India opens mineral and rare earth elements exploration to the private sector with 13 acreages up for auction, aiming to unlock untapped resources. The new policy encourages private investment, offering incentives like cost reimbursements and long-term mining leases. Around 25 companies showed interest, and the government hopes to create a thriving mineral exploration ecosystem.
title: Govt opens up exploration of 13 critical mineral blocks to private companies

description: Two forest watchers at Kanha National Park in Madhya Pradesh were arrested under UAPA for alleged Maoist ties, sparking fear among forest staff. Police claim they signaled Maoists about security force movements, while forest officials argue they were coerced by Maoists. Evidence suggests a deeper connection with the insurgents than initially admitted.
title: 2 forest watchers held for Red ties, face UAPA cases
ASI team reaches Sambhal to oversee maintenance work

description: The BJP criticized the TMC-led West Bengal government for allegedly banning Holi celebrations at Santiniketan, accusing CM Mamata Banerjee of appeasement politics. They urged Hindus to celebrate without fear. The state government clarified that there was no ban, but rather a request for environmental caution in protected areas. The BJP claimed the move was politically motivated.
title: BJP slams Didi for Santiniketan ‘Holi ban’, TMC denies any such prohibition

description: Kailash Nagare, a 2020 Young Farmer Award recipient, died by suicide, citing government negligence in a note he left behind. His death, attributed to unaddressed irrigation issues, led to significant unrest among farmers in his village, with demands for immediate government response. He is survived by his family.
title: Demand for irrigation denied, Maharashtra farmer kills self

description: Chhattisgarh has introduced a new policy focused on the surrender, relief, and rehabilitation of Maoists, victims of Naxal violence, and civilians aiding the police. The policy offers financial incentives, free education, job opportunities, and enhanced compensation for surrendered weapons. This initiative aims to accelerate the reduction of Left-wing extremism ahead of the 2026 deadline set by Home Minister Amit Shah.
title: Jobs, education pledge in Chhattisgarh Maoist surrender policy
‘Not among us’: Bijapur villagers protest rehab of dreaded Maoist

description: A parliamentary panel recommends lowering the age for Ayushman Vay Vandana Cards to 60 and suggests doubling healthcare coverage under Ayushman Bharat PM Jan Arogya Yojana to Rs 10 lakh per family. It advises proactive fund monitoring and linking fund release to states’ performance, and calls for revising package rates for hospitals to improve patient care.
title: Reduce age for senior citizen Ayushman cards to 60: Parliament panel

description: A PMLA court in Bhubaneswar has ordered the reimbursement of Rs 332 crore to victims of the Rose Valley chit fund scam in Odisha. The Enforcement Directorate had previously attached the group's assets, now valued at Rs 450 crore, and the Calcutta High Court's Assets Disposal Committee will oversee the fund distribution.
title: Return Rs 332 crore to Rose Valley scam victims in Odisha: Court
Watch: American Airlines passenger attacks crew, says 'Satan on plane'

description: In the case involving Kannada actor Ranya Rao, the CBI's FIR in the gold-smuggling racket has left the accused column blank, giving them flexibility in summoning individuals. The DRI suspects a coordinated syndicate between Dubai and India. The ED also raided multiple locations, including Ranya's flat, seizing documents and gadgets, pointing to high-level corruption.
title: Blank ‘accused column’ in CBI’s Ranya FIR worries netas & babus

description: In Babupur village, UP's Shahjahanpur, a class 5 student was fatally shot by a villager, Veerpal, and his son, Akash, after they mistook him for a thief while he was guarding his family's crop field. The incident occurred as the boy delivered dinner to his father. Both accused have been arrested and charged with murder.
title: Class 5 student guarding crop with dad mistaken for thief & shot dead
ED claims Rs 1,000 crore booze scam in Tamil Nadu

description: Militants hijacked a train in Pakistan's Balochistan, holding passengers hostage for nearly 36 hours. A successful military operation freed the hostages and eliminated over 30 militants. The BLA claimed responsibility, demanding the release of political prisoners. The attack left 21 civilian hostages and four military personnel dead, with the fate of 140 passengers uncertain.
title: 'Killed in front of our eyes': Survivors reveal how Pakistan train hijack unfolded
PLFI acting chief among 3 Maoists held in Jharkhand

description: The Uttar Pradesh Police Recruitment and Promotion Board announced results for 60,244 constable posts, including significant representation from women and various reservation categories. This concluded the largest state police recruitment, beginning with 48 lakh applications. Following a probe and re-examination, final selections were based on written scores, document verification, and physical tests. Successful candidates will undergo medical checks and training.
title: UP hires 60,244 cops in country’s biggest job drive

description: Vansh Katyal, a 22-year-old from Moradabad, was arrested for fatally hitting four labourers on Rajpur Road with a speeding Mercedes. The incident occurred while Katyal was on a joyride with his 12-year-old nephew. After the accident, he abandoned the vehicle and fled to Delhi. He is now in police custody.
title: UP trader’s son, 22, arrested for killing 4 during Doon joyride

description: Security measures in Sambhal, UP were heightened ahead of Holi. Shahi Jama Masjid and nine other mosques along the procession route were covered with tarpaulins to prevent colors from reaching religious sites. Over 1,000 people were bound down as a precautionary measure to maintain peace. Officials and community representatives ensured communal harmony.
title: Sambhal’s Jama Masjid covered with tarpaulin ahead of Holi
Agra techie suicide case: Wife on the run, her mother, sister arrested

description: Giannis Antetokounmpo’s status for the Milwaukee Bucks' critical matchup against the Los Angeles Lakers on March 13 is in doubt due to a calf injury. With key players like Damian Lillard and LeBron James also uncertain or ruled out, both teams face significant challenges. The game's results could hinge on Antetokounmpo's potential participation.
title: Will Giannis Antetokounmpo play tonight against the Los Angeles Lakers?

description: Talks to resolve a border dispute between Pakistan and Afghanistan broke down after the Afghan delegation accused Pakistan of not taking negotiations seriously. The disagreement caused the suspension of cross-border trade and transit, with significant financial losses for both nations. Tensions escalated following an exchange of fire that injured eight people and damaged property.
title: Afghan officials walk out of talks with Pak counterparts over border standoff

description: Pakistan’s military thwarted a suicide attack on a Frontier Corps camp in Jandola, Khyber Pakhtunkhwa, killing 10 TTP militants. The assault began with a massive explosion followed by a gun battle. No official casualty figures for security personnel or civilians were disclosed. This is the second major militant attack in Pakistan this week, highlighting rising regional security threats.
title: Attack on Jandola military base repelled, 10 militants killed

description: A study by SKIMS Medical College in Srinagar has found that the acknowledgments in medical theses in J&K often use repetitive, copy-pasted phrases. Common expressions thanking guides and invoking divine blessings appear frequently, indicating a lack of originality. The study highlights concerns about the inventiveness and independent thinking of future doctors in their research.
title: Ctrl+C, Ctrl+V: Copy-paste syndrome afflicts J&K medical theses

description: The Indian government is seeking to appeal the London high court's decision to block the extradition of Sanjay Bhandari, citing breaches of Articles 3 and 6 of the ECHR. They argue that the burden of proof issue is not a denial of justice and that they should have been allowed to provide more assurances about Bhandari's treatment in Tihar jail.
title: Delhi tries last-resort attempt to appeal Sanjay Bhandari extradition verditc
Foul play not ruled out in Pitt student Sudiksha Konanki's disappearance

description: Jammu and Kashmir CM Omar Abdullah has announced plans to transform Srinagar into a major tourist destination by promoting religious tourism and exploring lesser-known border spots like Gurez and Keran. With a focus on strengthening tourism infrastructure, the state has seen a rise in visitors, reaching 2.36 crore in 2024. Over 1,000 tourism projects have been completed this year.
title: J&K govt will promote religious, border tourism: Omar

description: J&K CM Omar Abdullah confirmed relatives' ownership of the Gulmarg hotel linked to a controversial fashion show during Ramzan, amidst political backlash. BJP accused him of ties due to models staying at Nedous Hotel. Amid inquiry, organisers apologised, citing unintentional offense, and the CM assured action if laws were broken.
title: Omar acknowledges relatives own Gulmarg hotel amid fashion show row

description: Pakistan hints at India’s involvement in the Balochistan train hijacking, linking attackers to handlers in Afghanistan allegedly sponsored by India. The incident, implicating the Balochistan Liberation Army, left 58 dead and highlights ongoing regional tensions and security issues. Afghanistan rejects Pakistan’s claims, and India is yet to respond to the allegations.
title: Pakistan hints at India role in deadly train hijacking

description: UK Prime Minister Keir Starmer announced the abolition of NHS England to reduce bureaucracy and bring it under government control. This move is aimed at shifting funds to frontline services, such as hiring nurses and doctors, and improving patient care. The integration process will be completed in two years, reducing overall staff numbers by 50 percent.
title: Starmer abolishes NHS England to bring health service back under govt control

description: Mumbai Indians advanced to their second Women's Premier League final after beating Gujarat Giants by 47 runs in the Eliminator. Nat Sciver-Brunt and Hayley Matthews scored 77 runs each, powering Mumbai to a total of 213 for four. Despite some resistance from Gujarat, Mumbai maintained their dominance, setting up a final against Delhi Capitals.
title: Mumbai Indians crush Gujarat Giants to set up WPL title clash vs Delhi Capitals

description: The US won't allow Canada ripping off anymore, Trump said. "We've been ripped off for years and we're not going to be ripped off anymore. No, I'm not going to bend at all -- aluminum or steel or cars," Trump told reporters when asked if he would back down. Trump said he loves Canada, Canada people but can't subsidize the country every year.
title: Trump says 'won't bend at all' on tariffs with Canada: 'Be our state, keep national anthem'

description: Virat Kohli has revealed a new hairstyle ahead of IPL 2025, showcasing a side fade and signature quiff. His sharply groomed beard enhances his sophisticated and commanding presence. Known for his style both on and off the field, Kohli continues to set grooming trends, inspiring fans ahead of the cricket season.
title: Virat Kohli unveils stylish new look ahead of IPL 2025
'Agree to ceasefire but ...': Putin may call Trump to clear up 'issues'

description: Dinesh Karthik praised Rohit Sharma and Virat Kohli for their match-winning performances in the ICC Champions Trophy and T20 World Cup finals, despite their prior form. He dismissed rumours of Rohit's retirement, lauding his legacy as a captain. Karthik expressed confidence in Yashasvi Jaiswal and Varun Chakaravarthy, and highlighted Shreyas Iyer's consistency under pressure.
title: 'Come the big game ...': Karthik on Rohit & Virat's ability to rise to the occasion

description: Union finance minister Nirmala Sitharaman criticized Tamil Nadu's CM MK Stalin for removing the rupee symbol from the state budget's logo, labeling it as an act of regional chauvinism. The Tamil Nadu government replaced the symbol to oppose the Centre's three-language policy under NEP, intensifying the ongoing language dispute.
title: 'Dangerous mindset': Sitharaman hits out at CM Stalin for replacing rupee symbol
Elderly couple murdered by neighbour during fight over his cattle damaging their crops

description: Solo Polyamory is a growing dating trend where individuals have multiple romantic partners without committing to any one of them. This lifestyle focuses on personal freedom and self-reliance, appealing to those who avoid conventional relationships. Despite the attraction to independence, participants might eventually face loneliness and a lack of deep connections impacting their mental well-being.
title: Solo Polyamory: How this new dating trend is redefining modern love

description: The Balochistan Liberation Army (BLA) claims it still holds hostages from the Jaffar Express, contrary to Pakistan military's statement of resolving the crisis. BLA alleges the military deceived the public and asserts ongoing conflict after Pakistan reported freeing 340 passengers, amid conflicting death toll reports.
title: Train siege standoff still on? BLA refutes Pak army's claim
Bihar cop dies as villagers attack police team, free arrested criminal

description: The Central Board of Secondary Education (CBSE) has confirmed that the Class 12 Hindi board exams will proceed on March 15, 2025, despite potential Holi celebrations in some regions. However, students facing difficulties can opt for a rescheduled test. This aligns with CBSE’s existing policy for athletes, ensuring fairness while maintaining the examination schedule.
title: Class 12 students missing Mar 15 Hindi exam due to Holi can take exam again

description: Harry Brook has been banned from the IPL for two seasons after pulling out of the 2025 edition. The BCCI enforces a two-year ban for overseas players who withdraw after being picked at the auction. Brook opted out to focus on his England career and recharge after a busy period, apologizing to Delhi Capitals and their fans.
title: England batter Harry Brook faces two-year IPL ban

description: Former West Indies cricketer Dwayne Bravo, now a mentor at Kolkata Knight Riders, aims to blend the successful strategies of his predecessor Gautam Gambhir with his own for the upcoming IPL. Bravo, who is excited about collaborating with Shah Rukh Khan and the KKR team, emphasises maintaining team stability and building on the previous season's success.
title: 'Gambhir had his style, I have my style': New KKR mentor Dwayne Bravo

description: Celebrate this year’s Holi with all your friends and family, and forward them a lovely special from our curated Holi wishes and messages list. Make their day more blissful, filled with colours of joy and happiness.
title: Happy Holi 2025: Wishes, messages, quotes, and images

description: A 32-year-old man in Connecticut was rescued after setting his house on fire to escape 20 years of captivity and abuse by his stepmother, Kimberly Sullivan. Having been held in an unheated, airless room, he endured severe malnutrition and unsanitary conditions. Sullivan faces charges including cruelty and kidnapping. The victim was found weighing less than 70 pounds.
title: House of horror: US man drinks from toilet bowl as stepmom holds him captive for 20 years

description: Trump's tariffs on steel and aluminum have led to an international boycott of US goods. European and Canadian consumers are rejecting American products in response to perceived unfair trade practices. The boycott has affected various industries, including liquor, automobiles, and tourism. If the boycott continues, American brands may need to rebrand or relocate manufacturing.
title: 'This chaos has to stop': Trump's tariffs prompt 'boycott USA' backlash

description: Diplomatic tensions between India and Bangladesh persist, but their military cooperation remains robust. The recent 'Bongosagar' naval exercise showcased joint efforts to tackle maritime challenges and improve operational coordination, highlighting the ongoing strategic importance of collaboration despite regional geopolitical complexities.
title: Amid ongoing diplomatic chill, India & Bangladesh conduct naval exercise
'Don't forcibly apply colours': UP CM says 'celebrate Holi in harmony'

description: Canadians who cross the northern border by land and stay for over 30 days do not need to register with the federal government. However, the new rule would require them to fill out a different form to enter the US, which is not a visa. Canadians never needed any form or visa to enter the US for casual travelling, tourism, shopping etc.
title: New rule for Canadians staying in the US for over 30 days amid Donald Trump's tariff war
Prez okays FIR against AAP's Sisodia, Jain in Rs 1,300 cr classroom scam case

description: US President Donald Trump’s early moves in his second term disrupted global diplomacy, alienated allies, and uplifted rivals. Key changes included abandoning Ukraine, floating territorial expansions, pressuring Nato, and reducing foreign aid under Elon Musk’s guidance. This shift has heightened European defense discussions and empowered China and Russia on the global stage.
title: Territory, tariffs and chaos: 10 ways Trump shook the world in 50 days

description: PDP chairperson Mehbooba Mufti criticized the Uttar Pradesh CM for allegedly creating divisions between Hindus and Muslims. She warned this division could deteriorate the communal harmony, similar to Pakistan under Zia-ul-Haq. With Holi coinciding with Ramzan, leaders advised Muslims to stay indoors to avoid conflict.
title: Holi-Jumma row: Mehbooba compares UP CM Yogi to Pak dictator

description: Finance Minister Nirmala Sitharaman's Union Budget 2025 introduced significant modifications to TDS regulations. The changes include increased TDS thresholds for senior citizens, regular citizens, commission earners, and investors, effective from April 1, 2025.
title: New TDS rules from April 1, 2025: Check out details

description: Jamie Dimon of JPMorgan Chase appears to be rethinking his support for Trump's tariffs amid US stock market decline, acknowledging their uncertainty for companies. Dimon had earlier defended them at WEF, viewing tariffs as economic tools. BlackRock CEO Larry Fink similarly expressed mixed concerns, seeing potential long-term benefits despite immediate economic strain.
title: Trump Tariffs: From 'Get over it' to 'I don't ...', has JPMorgan Chase CEO changed

description: Former cricketer Navjot Singh Sidhu supports Rohit Sharma as India's Test captain despite criticism over his recent form. Sidhu highlights Sharma's experience and previous successes, urging for a blend of seasoned players like Rohit, Virat Kohli, and KL Rahul with younger talents until the 2027 ODI World Cup to build a strong team.
title: 'You should have a replacement first': Sidhu backs Rohit to lead India in England Tests

description: Madhya Pradesh government railway police have detained 18 passengers suspected of being coerced into converting to Christianity through promises of financial rewards, educational opportunities, and jobs abroad. The detentions occurred at Gwalior and Vidisha stations following a tip-off from Bajrang Dal officials.
title: Madhya Pradesh GRP takes 18 off train to stop their ‘conversion'

description: Aamir Khan introduced his new girlfriend, Gauri, during his 60th birthday celebration. Previously married to Reena Dutta and Kiran Rao, Aamir has three children: Ira, Junaid, and Azad. Despite their separation, Aamir and Kiran maintain a professional and personal connection, emphasizing the importance of family and mutual respect. Aamir's son Junaid recently debuted in films.
title: Aamir Khan introduces his 'girlfriend' Gauri on his 60th birthday

description: Shark Tank India judge Anupam Mittal reacted to Temasek’s acquisition of a 9-10% stake in Haldiram's, valuing it at nearly $10 billion. This deal marks significant foreign investment in India's FMCG sector, with Temasek aiming to expand its footprint in the rapidly growing market.
title: Anupam Mittal on Singapore's Temasek buying 10% stake in Haldiram for $10 billion

description: Tehrik-e-Taliban Pakistan (TTP) executed a suicide attack on the Jandola military base in Khyber Pakhtunkhwa, leading to the Pakistan Army killing eight to nine militants. Following the explosion, heavy gunfire ensued near the Frontier Corps camp in South Waziristan. This incident trails the Baloch Liberation Army's recent hijacking of the Jaffar Express in the Bolan Valley.
title: Days after train siege, terrorists attack army camp in Pakistan

description: ​​Khalil’s arrest and possible deportation aren’t just about one man with an opinion the government doesn’t like; they’re about the bigger question of whether the First Amendment is truly for everyone or just for those who pass the political vibe check. If free speech really is the bedrock of democracy, why is a lawful permanent resident being shown the door for actually using it?
title: How Palestine activist Mahmoud Khalil exposed Trump & Musk on free speech

description: The arrest and potential deportation of Columbia graduate student Mahmoud Khalil have sparked outrage, raising concerns about green card holders’ rights in the US. Accused of posing a foreign policy risk, Khalil's pro-Palestinian activism led to his detention by ICE. A federal judge has temporarily blocked his deportation, but his future remains uncertain.
title: Khalil faces deportation: Should students in US with green cards be worried?

description: US President Donald Trump has threatened to impose a 200 per cent tariff on French and European Union alcoholic products in response to the EU's 50 per cent tariff on American whiskey. The trade dispute escalates as the EU plans counter-tariffs worth €26 billion on various US goods.
title: 'Most hostile': Trump threatens 200% tariff on European alcohol

description: Former Pakistan captain Mohammad Hafeez claims Abdul Razzaq was a better all-rounder than India's Hardik Pandya, citing Razzaq's untapped potential and past performances. Hafeez's views are echoed by Shoaib Akhtar, who praises Razzaq's impactful playing days and criticises the lack of recognition for Razzaq and Azhar Mahmood despite their consistent contributions.
title: Abdul Razzaq better all-rounder than Hardik Pandya: Ex-Pak captain

description: Tamil Nadu Chief Minister MK Stalin replaced the rupee symbol with a Tamil script in the state budget amidst a controversy over 'Hindi imposition.' The rupee symbol was originally designed by Tamilian Udaya Kumar, whose work incorporated both Indian and universal design features.
title: Meet TN man who designed Rupee symbol & his DMK connection

description: The Detroit Red Wings ended a six-game losing streak by defeating the Buffalo Sabres 7-3. Patrick Kane shined with two goals and three assists. The third period featured intense fights, including notable brawls involving Alex Tuch and Michael Rasmussen, leading to 134 penalty minutes. Buffalo's frustration was evident, but Detroit secured a morale-boosting victory.
title: Patrick Kane shines in Red Wings' 7-3 victory over the Buffalo Sabres

description: UK Prime Minister Keir Starmer announces that NHS England will be abolished, placing the NHS back under direct government control to cut bureaucracy and eliminate duplication. The decision aims to redirect funds to frontline services and bring NHS oversight back to politicians.
title: UK scraps NHS England, puts healthcare back under govt control

description: President Trump shared an article featuring the Pink Triangle, once a Nazi symbol for gay men in concentration camps. His administration has rapidly altered LGBTQ+ policies, including banning transgender individuals from military service. The article highlights stark differences between Trump's military and Biden's, emphasizing aggression. The Pink Triangle's connection to the Holocaust raises significant concerns.
title: What is 'Pink Triangle'? Nazi era anti-LGBTQ symbol shared by Trump

description: Actress Bhagyashree recently sustained a serious forehead injury requiring surgery while playing pickleball. Despite being away from mainstream cinema after 'Maine Pyar Kiya', she has made notable comebacks. Fans have wished her a speedy recovery through social media.
title: Bhagyashree undergoes surgery after pickleball injury, gets 13 stitches

description: Epic Games CEO Tim Sweeney supports Elon Musk's claims that protests against Tesla are funded by billionaire donors, connecting it to Epic's battle with Big Tech. Sweeney criticizes deceptive funding of anti-Tesla campaigns and their violent fringes. Protests have intensified globally, reflecting dissatisfaction with Musk's political engagements, leading to notable incidents and public displays of disapproval.
title: Elon Musk claims Soros, Hoffman fund Tesla protests; Fortnite CEO agrees

description: Elon Musk's Starlink partners with India's Reliance Jio and Bharti Airtel to enhance digital infrastructure. These alliances aim to supply satellite internet services across India, pending regulatory approvals, with a focus on improving connectivity in remote regions for nearly 950 million internet users.
title: Harsh Goenka ‘names’ India's new '3M': Musk, Mittal and Mukesh

description: Hyderabad police imposed restrictions for Holi celebrations, restricting group movement of vehicles and throwing colors on unwilling persons. BJP MLA Raja Singh criticized the move, calling it discriminatory and anti-Hindu, alleging influence from the Congress government. Restrictions are in effect from March 13 to March 15, with closure of wine shops and bars on March 14.
title: Hyderabad: Restrictions on Holi celebrations imposed, BJP calls it 'Tughlaq farman'

description: Rishabh Pant's sister Sakshi married Ankit Chaudhary in a grand Mussoorie wedding. Cricket stars, including MS Dhoni, Suresh Raina, and Gautam Gambhir, attended and entertained with dance and singing. Notable moments included Pant's serenade and Dhoni's dance to "Dama Dam Mast Qalandar." The event was a joyous celebration filled with love and cricketing camaraderie.
title: Inside Pant's sister's wedding: Dhoni, Raina & cricketer crew steal the show

description: Anurag Kashyap's departure from Bollywood underscores his frustration with the industry's focus on profit over creativity. Renowned for his unorthodox storytelling, Kashyap seeks a fulfilling environment in regional cinemas. This shift points to a broader trend where filmmakers pursue creative freedom beyond Bollywood's commercial constraints, reshaping the landscape of Indian cinema.
title: Is Anurag Kashyap's exit a wake-up call for Bollywood?

description: On March 12, 2025, Rishabh Pant's sister, Sakshi Pant, married her long-time partner Ankit Choudhary in a traditional Hindu ceremony. The wedding, attended by notable cricketers, featured Sakshi in a red lehenga and traditional Kumaoni jewellery, while Ankit wore an ivory Sherwani. The couple, who dated for ten years, got engaged in January 2024.
title: Rishabh Pant's sister Sakshi turns traditional Kumaoni bride on her wedding

description: Russian forces have regained control of Sudzha in the Kursk region from Ukrainian forces. This follows President Vladimir Putin's visit, advocating for swift liberation, and coincides with U.S.-Ukrainian ceasefire talks. The regainment threatens Ukraine's bargaining position amid ongoing negotiations.
title: Ukraine war: Russia gets key bargaining chip as US calls for truce

description: The Tata Tiago NRG features new silver skid plates on both the front and rear bumpers, along with newly designed 15-inch wheel covers for the steel wheels. In addition to these updates, the NRG distinguishes itself from the standard Tiago with distinctive black side cladding, black roof rails, and an NRG emblem adorning the tailgate.
title: 2025 Tata Tiago NRG launched at Rs 7.2L: How's it different from regular model

description: Banks in various states will observe closures on March 13 and 14, 2025, due to Holi celebrations as per RBI guidelines. Physical branches will be closed, but digital banking services, including UPI payments and ATM operations, will remain available.
title: Are banks closed on March 13, 14 and 15? Check state-wise holiday list

description: Four family members, including a doctor, his wife, and two sons, were found dead by hanging in their Anna Nagar West home. Initial investigations suggest the doctor faced financial difficulties in his scan business, possibly leading to their tragic deaths. The bodies were discovered by their driver, and the police have registered a case.
title: 'Huge loss in business': Doctor, wife, and two sons found hanging at Chennai house

description: Infosys addressed employee concerns over its new work-from-office mandate, which requires at least 10 days in the office each month. The company clarified that non-compliance prompts managerial approval for extra WFH days, avoiding automatic leave deduction.
title: Infosys HR clarifies 'System Intervention' after WFO policy raises ‘concerns’

description: Cricketer Rishabh Pant recently attended the wedding of his sister Sakshi Pant to Ankit Choudary in Mussoorie. The event garnered attention not only for the presence of several famous cricketers but also due to the surprising resemblance between Rishabh and his new brother-in-law Ankit.
title: People shocked at striking similarity between Rishabh Pant and his sister's husband

description: Congress leader Tikaram Jully caused controversy by labeling Madhuri Dixit as a 'second-grade star' during a discussion about the IIFA event's benefits to Rajasthan. He claimed no top-tier actors, aside from Shah Rukh Khan, attended. BJP MLA Balmukund Acharya defended the event's importance.
title: ‘Second-grade actor’: Congress MLA’s remark on Madhuri Dixit stirs row

description: The Tamil Nadu government, led by MK Stalin, has replaced the Rupee symbol with the Tamil script 'ரூ' for the state's 2025-26 budget, sparking a renewed language debate with the Centre. BJP leaders criticized this decision, emphasizing the national significance of the Rupee symbol, initially designed by a Tamilian.
title: Stalin govt replaces rupee symbol with Tamil letter in budget amid language row

description: Holi, the vibrant Indian festival, encourages kids to play outdoors, promoting physical and emotional well-being. It connects children to their cultural heritage through traditional stories and songs, fostering community spirit and inclusivity. Celebrated with family, it strengthens bonds and creates cherished memories. Traditional songs like 'Holi Hai' and 'Holi Khele Raghuveera' add to the festive joy.
title: The beauty of Phag! 6 traditional Holi songs all kids should know

description: Alia Bhatt began her 32nd birthday celebrations with a cake-cutting event with the media and husband Ranbir Kapoor. Ranbir's playful smearing of cake on Alia's nose delighted fans. The couple will appear together in 'Love & War', with Alia embracing a no-makeup look. The upcoming film is set for release in 2026.
title: Watch: Alia’s reaction as Ranbir smears cake on her face at pre-birthday celebrations

description: Firefly Aerospace's Blue Ghost lander successfully touched down on the moon, deploying experiments like the LISTER drill and NASA's Lunar Magnetotelluric Sounder. The lander will conclude its mission on March 16, after achieving its objectives and capturing images to study lunar dust at sunset.
title: Watch: Sparks fly as Firefly's Blue Ghost lander drills into moon's surface

description: Yellowstone National Park, renowned for its geothermal features, poses severe dangers in restricted areas. The tragic death of Colin Scott, who fell into a boiling acidic hot spring while filming, underscores the lethal risks of ignoring warnings. Despite posted signs, some visitors venture off trails, risking severe injuries or fatalities. Authorities urge adherence to the park's safety guidelines.
title: Man tries to take a 'hot-pot' at the Yellowstone National Park, dies

description: Gurdeep Singh, 103, spent over 19 months in jail after his sons falsely claimed to be attending court hearings, leading to his arrest. The elderly farmer wanted to donate land to a gurdwara, which his sons opposed. An NGO eventually secured his release.
title: Sons make man, 103, spend 19 months in jail to stop land donation to gurdwara in UP

description: According to these karigars, special care is taken while stitching costumes for God, including purity, and cleanliness. The karigars say that their main aim is to make Banke Bihari happy. They also said that while Krishna's costume takes only 1-2 days, Radha Rani's lehenga can take upto a week, and can cost anywhere between 8-10,000
title: Communal harmony at its best: 'Poshaks' of Lord Krishna made in a mosque, temple rejects call to ban them: reports

description: Elon Musk, CEO of Tesla, expressed emotional strain in a Fox Business interview due to challenges with his companies and Tesla’s stock experiencing a significant decline. Increased government involvement and attacks on Tesla facilities have raised investor concerns. Musk managing multiple ventures with difficulty, as seen in the video, suggests he is under immense pressure.
title: Elon Musk seems to be almost 'choking' in interview talking about Tesla struggles

description: Intel has named Lip-Bu Tan as its new CEO, with a vision to restore the company's industry standing. Tan emphasized a three-part philosophy and a focus on engineering excellence, customer satisfaction, and teamwork as key strategies to overcome recent challenges and drive future success.
title: Intel new CEO Lip-Bu Tan's memo to employees: 'I am joining because…'

description: N R Narayana Murthy, Infosys Co-Founder, stressed job creation by innovative entrepreneurs as the solution to poverty, not freebies. He urged entrepreneurs to build businesses generating employment, while expressing concerns over India's cash transfers to 80 crore people. Murthy also criticized many artificial intelligence solutions as outdated, emphasizing the need for genuine innovation.
title: No country has beaten poverty with freebies: Narayana Murthy at Mumbai event

description: The Enforcement Directorate conducted multiple raids in Karnataka in connection with a gold smuggling case involving actress Ranya Rao, who was arrested for attempting to smuggle gold from Dubai. Investigations point to a possible nexus with a smuggling syndicate, as additional officials and foreign nationals are also implicated.
title: Ranya Rao gold smuggling case: ED raids multiple locations in Bengaluru, other places

description: A man in Upparagudem village, Mahabubabad district, killed his wife after she refused to cook mutton curry, leading to a fatal altercation. The victim, M Kalavathi, died from a head injury inflicted by her husband, M Balu, who has been taken into police custody.
title: Man kills wife for refusing to cook mutton curry in Telangana

description: An 80-year-old woman donated her kidney to her 59-year-old son with end-stage renal disease. The transplant was successfully conducted by Dr. HS Bhatyal and his team at BLK-Max Super Speciality Hospital. Both the mother and son have recovered well and were discharged a few days after the surgery. This case emphasizes the potential of modern medicine.
title: 80 year old mother donates kidney to her son in a remarkable story of love

description: Suchir Balaji's mother challenges the suicide ruling over her son’s death, citing inconsistencies and potential foul play. She questions the use of sedatives and faulty CCTV footage. Despite authorities maintaining the suicide verdict, the family persists in seeking justice with independent investigations, drawing support from figures like Elon Musk who also suspects foul play.
title: Suchir Balaji's mother shares pic from day of his death, alleges 'murder'

description: A college student in Banaskantha was allegedly raped repeatedly by seven men who blackmailed her with a nude video filmed in Nov 2023. They coerced her over 16 months, with a case now registered against the accused under various charges, including repeated rape and criminal intimidation.
title: 20-year-old college student gang raped by 7 for 16 months in Gujarat

description: Mumbai's Lilavati Hospital trust accused former trustees of misappropriating over Rs 1,500 crore and performing black magic on hospital premises. A forensic audit revealed large-scale financial irregularities. Multiple FIRs have been lodged, and the Economic Offences Wing is investigating. The hospital trust is urging swift action to ensure responsible individuals are held accountable.
title: 7 urns with human hair, skulls: 'Rs 1500cr fraud' at Lilavati Hosp with black magic twist

description: AB de Villiers praised Rohit Sharma for his leadership and batting after India's four-wicket victory over New Zealand in the ICC Champions Trophy final. Rohit top-scored with 76 runs and was named Player of the Final. De Villiers emphasised Rohit's impressive record and growth, dismissing retirement rumours and highlighting his significant contributions to Indian cricket.
title: AB de Villiers on Rohit Sharma: 'Why would he retire?'

description: A British national was allegedly raped and molested at a hotel in South West Delhi's Mahipalpur, leading to the arrest of a man and a housekeeping staff member. The woman, who met the accused through social media and arrived in India earlier this month, reported the incident to the police.
title: British woman raped at south Delhi hotel by man she met on Instagram

description: Mitchell Starc praised the depth of Indian cricket, stating that India is the only nation capable of fielding competitive teams in all three formats simultaneously. He acknowledged IPL's impact but emphasized the overall talent in Indian cricket.
title: 'India can have T20I, ODI & Test team play on same day'

description: Jeweller Adesh Kumar Jain said, "This is an old tradition in which this 'Pichkari' is gifted among a newly married couple's family, where the bride's family gifts it to the groom's family as a pledge... Its price ranges from about Rs 8000 to Rs 1 lakh..."
title: Lucknow shop sells luxurious silver pichkari worth Rs 1 lakh for Holi
'They took soldiers, executed them': Survivors recall Pak train hijacking ordeal

description: President Trump has warned Russia of severe financial repercussions if it does not agree to the proposed ceasefire in Ukraine. While US negotiators are en route to Russia, Ukrainian President Zelenskyy remains skeptical. Trump remains hopeful for a diplomatic resolution, while Vice President Vance and other key officials continue discussions with Russia to finalize the ceasefire plan.
title: 'Could do things very bad for Russia': Trump warns Putin amid ceasefire talks

description: Astronaut Sunita Williams has been stranded in space since June 6 due to a technical fault in the Boeing Starliner spacecraft. Attempts to bring her back with SpaceX's Crew 10 mission were unsuccessful. Williams, who misses her family, especially her pet, is facing mental and physical challenges while awaiting a safe return.
title: In her first post on X, Sunita Williams reveals what she misses the most while in space

description: Elon Musk reshared a video where JP Morgan Chase CEO Jamie Dimon praises him, calling Musk 'our Einstein' for his work with SpaceX, Tesla, and Neuralink. Dimon also shared strong views on government efficiency and accountability. “I think it is completely rational for someone to look at our government and say it's been ineffective,” he remarked.
title: JP Morgan Chase CEO Jamie Dimon has this Thanks and All the Best message for Elon Musk

description: The Karnataka School Examination and Assessment Board (KSEAB) has released admit cards for the SSLC exams, which will be held from March 20 to April 2, 2025. Schools must verify student details by March 17. Hall tickets can be downloaded online or collected from schools. Principals will be accountable for errors, and special accommodations must be confirmed in advance.
title: Karnataka SSLC hall ticket 2025: Check key details to access the admit card

description: In Salt Lake, a collision between a motorist and a biker escalated into a chase, resulting in the biker's death. The biker, Aiyaz Hussain, lost control and skidded on an uneven, poorly lit road. Local residents apprehended the motorist, Piyush Agarwal, who was later arrested for causing death due to negligence and sent to jail custody.
title: Kolkata horror: Late-night road rage ends in biker’s death, motorist held

description: Ranya Rao, a Kannada film starlet, is under investigation for her alleged involvement in a Rs 12.56 crore gold smuggling case, using VIP services at the Bengaluru airport. Her stepfather, a senior police officer, is also being scrutinized for his role in the scandal.
title: Ranya Rao gold case: Why Karnataka home dept backtracked from CID probe

description: The Union Ministry of Youth Affairs and Sports restored the Wrestling Federation of India's recognition, lifting its suspension. Former WFI President, Brij Bhushan Sharan Singh shared his views on the decision. The suspension was initially imposed due to procedural lapses and accusations of sexual harassment against Singh, but has now been lifted to benefit the sport and its athletes.
title: '99.9% of people are happy': Brij Bhushan on WFI ban lift

description: A Sydney District Court jury acquitted former Australia Test cricketer Stuart MacGill of involvement in a significant commercial drug deal but convicted him on a lesser charge tied to drug supply. Despite arranging a meeting, MacGill claimed he was unaware of the cocaine transaction arranged by his supplier and brother-in-law.
title: Former Aus cricketer MacGill found guilty in cocaine deal

description: Holika Dahan, a significant Hindu festival, will be observed on March 13, 2025. The festival symbolizes the triumph of good over evil and includes specific rituals. The auspicious time for the rituals begins after Bhadra Kaal and continues into Pradosh Kaal. Essential materials and mantras are also suggested for a spiritually fulfilling celebration.
title: Holika Dahan 2025: Your guide to shubh muhurat, pooja vidhi and mantras

description: Meta CEO Mark Zuckerberg visited the White House to discuss American technology leadership with Trump administration officials. The visit followed Meta's recent advancements in AI and ongoing development of its first internally designed chip, in collaboration with TSMC.
title: Mark Zuckerberg visits White House for second meeting with Donald Trump

description: NASA astronaut Butch Wilmore's daughter shared a poignant video revealing his missed moments due to his extended space mission. Wilmore and Sunita Williams are expected to return from the ISS by March 16, 2025, after a rescheduled launch. The family has been waiting since June, marking significant life events in his absence, including a wedding anniversary.
title: NASA astronaut Butch Wilmore's daughter shares why she's missing him more than ever now

description: Yeh Rishta Kya Kehlata Hai has aired for over 15 years, starring Hina Khan and Karan Mehra as iconic characters Akshara and Naitik. Producer Rajan Shahi shared insights on preparing Hina for the role, involving extensive efforts and overcoming channel disapprovals. Despite past conflicts, Hina still acknowledges his support. The duo's storyline remains beloved.
title: Rajan Shahi talks about managing Hina Khan's spa, waxing and other expenses

description: Former Haryana CM Bhupinder Singh Hooda downplayed BJP's victory in the municipal elections, noting that the party has won before. Haryana CM Nayab Singh Saini commended local body's role in achieving PM Modi's vision. BJP secured nine mayoral posts, except in Manesar. In Faridabad, Mayor-elect Parveen Joshi pledged to address local issues.
title: 'What's new?': Bhupinder Hooda plays down BJP’s victory in local elections

description: The West Bengal government has banned Holi celebrations at Sonajhuri Haat in Santiniketan due to concerns over potential damage to the area's greenery. Authorities have placed banners advising visitors not to park vehicles or celebrate Holi there, citing its proximity to Visva Bharati University, a UNESCO World Heritage site.
title: 'Damage to trees': WB govt imposes ban on Holi celebrations in Santiniketan

description: Oliver Miller, a former NBA center and Arkansas Razorbacks legend, passed away at 54. Known as 'The Big O,' he was vital in Arkansas' 1990 Final Four run and enjoyed a nine-year NBA career. His contributions were acknowledged by former teams and fans alike.
title: Former NBA center and Arkansas Razorbacks legend Oliver Miller passes away at 54

description: Balochistan's long-standing insurgency reached a new level, with the Baluch Liberation Army seizing a passenger train. The militants killed 21 passengers before being overpowered by Pakistani forces. The BLA fights for independence and more control over Balochistan's resources, claiming support from India. This attack might weaken their support despite drawing significant attention.
title: Pakistan train attack: Why is there an increase in attacks in Balochistan?

description: During the annual St. Patrick's Day celebration at the White House, President Trump praised Vice President JD Vance's shamrock-themed socks, creating a lighthearted moment that amused attendees. The conversation, which initially focused on inflation, shifted to Vance's festive accessories, garnering laughter and attention.
title: 'What’s with these socks': Trump teases JD Vance in Oval Office; watch video

description: Wayne Gretzky, an iconic NHL player who retired in 1999 with 61 NHL records, discussed his favorite record with comedian Theo Von. Gretzky cherished his achievement of scoring 50 goals in 39 games during the 1981-82 season, a record he considers almost unbreakable. His impressive career set new benchmarks in ice hockey history.
title: “Hardest record to break”: Wayne Gretzky reveals his favorite all-time NHL record

description: US President Donald Trump announced that high-level negotiators are headed to Russia to discuss a ceasefire in Ukraine following Kyiv's agreement to a US-backed 30-day truce. Trump emphasized diplomacy but warned of possible sanctions if Russia does not cooperate.
title: 'It's up to Russia now': US team headed to Moscow for Ukraine ceasefire talks

description: Ragini Khanna discussed why she left The Kapil Sharma Show. She stated that the show offered nothing fresh and only gave her roles where women wore revealing clothes. This objectification made her uncomfortable. She also mentioned that long working hours on TV affected her health, giving her severe gastroenteritis.
title: Ragini Khanna recalls quitting The Kapil Sharma Show because she didn't want to play the 'hot girl'

description: Astronauts returning from space experience 'baby feet,' where their soles become hypersensitive due to microgravity. This is caused by the lack of weight-bearing exercises. Recovery involves gradual re-acclimatization to pressure, specific exercises, balance training, and proper hydration. Other effects include puffy faces, muscle loss, and dizziness. Rehabilitation is critical for a complete recovery.
title: Sunita Williams, Butch Wilmore likely to have 'baby feet' after arrival on earth

description: Cricketer Shubman Gill shared a 2023 video showcasing Team India, including Virat Kohli and Rohit Sharma, celebrating Holi on a bus before their fourth Test against Australia. The celebration featured Amitabh Bachchan's iconic Holi song 'Rang Barse Bhige Chunar Wali' from the movie 'Silsila,' which added to the festive spirit as the team danced and cheered.
title: When Kohli, Gill and others brought Holi vibe with THIS Amitabh song

description: A speeding Mercedes with a Chandigarh registration number killed four people and critically injured two others near Sai Baba Temple on Rajpur Road in Dehradun. The driver fled the scene. Authorities are working to identify the driver and have linked 11-12 vehicles to the case.
title: 4 dead as speeding Mercedes wreaks havoc on Dehradun road, driver flees

description: Top stock market recommendations: Aakash K Hindocha of Nuvama Professional Clients Group recommends buying DLF, SRF, and Adani Ports. Nifty is poised for an upward journey towards 22800+, while Bank Nifty faces bearish pressures.
title: Top stocks to buy today: Stock recommendations for March 13

description: ‘Chhaava,’ the historical drama starring Vicky Kaushal, continues to impress at the box office, hitting Rs. 535.55 crore in just 27 days. Directed by Laxman Utekar, the film has received praise for its gripping plot and Kaushal's powerful performance. With Holi festivities approaching, further growth is anticipated despite experiencing slower weekdays.
title: ‘Chhaava’ collection: Vicky Kaushal's film earns over Rs 535 crore

description: Haryana has seen a six-fold increase in poverty over the past five years, with 51.83 lakh families now below the poverty line. Despite the state government's various upliftment schemes, the data suggests that over two crore people in Haryana live in poverty, contrasting with claims of prosperity.
title: Spike in Haryana poverty? Data shows 6-time jump in BPL families in 5 years

description: Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath's posters at a rally in Kathmandu supporting the former Nepal king sparked a stir, highlighting the historical ties between Gorakhsh Peeth and the Shah Dynasty. Yogi has previously advocated for Nepal's Hindu nation status. A follower, Pradeep Bikram Rana, fled to Gorakhpur, citing persecution in Kathmandu.
title: Why UP CM Yogi Adityanath became a ‘poster boy’ in Nepal rally

description: A street dog in Rewa, Madhya Pradesh, was seen roaming with a dead newborn in its jaws, attracting significant attention after a video circulated on social media. Authorities are investigating the incident, which marks the third instance of a dead newborn being abandoned in the district within the past three weeks.
title: Madhya Pradesh horror: Dead baby in jaws of a stray dog

description: Allahabad High Court has ordered the Archaeological Survey of India (ASI) to whitewash the Sambhal Jama Masjid's outer facade and the mosque committee to cover the expenses within a week. The decision followed a petition by the mosque management committee. The court will reevaluate the situation on April 8, considering further conditions set by the ASI report.
title: ASI can whitewash Sambhal mosque facade: Allahabad high court

description: Choti Holi, or Holika Dahan, celebrates the triumph of good over evil and precedes the Holi festival. It involves lighting bonfires, performing rituals, and sharing wishes. The festival symbolizes the victory of righteousness through the legend of Prahlad and Holika. Engage in the festivities with devotion, joy, and colorful celebrations.
title: Choti Holi 2025: Wishes, quotes & status

description: Following the return of a killed youth's body to his family in Manipur's Kangpokpi, authorities anticipate an end to protests and blockades in the district. However, tensions persist as the Kuki-Zo community demands a separate hill state, conflicting with the Constitutional framework. Efforts are ongoing to engage with both Meitei and Kuki-Zo communities for a resolution within Constitutional bounds.
title: Manipur talks stuck as Kukis insist on ‘separate hill state’

description: Airtel and Reliance Jio have announced deals to market Elon Musk's Starlink satellite internet in India, pending regulatory approvals. These partnerships aim to enhance network coverage, especially in rural and remote areas where connectivity is limited. Satellite internet services will, however, be more expensive and initially cater to enterprise sectors.
title: Musk, Mittal, now Mukesh: Jio too unveils Starlink deal

description: Pakistan cricket is facing turmoil after an early exit from the Champions Trophy 2025. Mickey Arthur criticises the instability despite talented players and quality coaches like Jason Gillespie and Gary Kirsten. Internal conflicts and media agendas are blamed for undermining efforts. Babar Azam and Mohammad Rizwan have been dropped for the upcoming T20I series against New Zealand.
title: 'Pakistan is its worst enemy': Arthur backs Gillespie after ‘clown’ jab
Sangh spreading ‘cancer’, says Bapu grandson, gets heckled

description: Nasa has postponed the Nasa-SpaceX Crew-10 mission due to hydraulic system issues discovered before launch. This delay impacts the return of two astronauts from the International Space Station. The replacement crew, led by Nasa astronaut Anne McClain, will include members from Japan and Russia. The updated launch might occur by Thursday night, subject to conditions.
title: SpaceX delays mission to bring back Nasa astronaut Sunita Williams

description: A video of MS Dhoni and Rishabh Pant singing 'Tu Jaane Na' at Sakshi Pant's sangeet has gone viral. The ceremony, held in Dehradun, featured several cricket stars. Dhoni attended with his wife Sakshi, and Pant joined fresh from winning the Champions Trophy. More cricketers like Rohit Sharma and Virat Kohli are expected at the wedding.
title: Viral video: Dhoni, Pant sing their hearts out to 'Tu Jaane Na'
Govt to probe price disparity plaints against cab aggregators

description: Two woman journalists, Pogadadanda Revathi and Bandi Sandhya, were arrested in Hyderabad for circulating a derogatory video about Telangana CM A Revanth Reddy. The video, involving an elderly farmer, led to a complaint from the Congress’s social media cell. Their arrest sparked criticism from BRS's KT Rama Rao, questioning Congress's stance on free speech.
title: 2 scribes held for ‘derogatory content’ against Telangana CM

description: The government's Poshan Tracker data reveals that as of February, 8.8 crore children aged 0-6 years were enrolled in Anganwadis. Out of them, 8.5 crore children were measured on growth parameters. The Ministry highlights a 37.7% stunting rate and 17.1% underweight rate among these children. The government's data shows improvement compared to National Family Health Surveys.
title: 38% of U-6 kids stunted, 17% underweight: Govt

description: The post-mortem reports of three youths from Kathua who were found dead suggest they died from trauma injuries caused by an accidental fall. There were no signs of physical assault or gunshot wounds, ruling out a terrorist attack. They were last in contact with family members before losing their way to a wedding, with alcohol found at the scene.
title: Autopsy report rules out ‘terror hit’ angle in Kathua deaths

description: CBI raided the premises of a retired NCLT official in a bribery case involving a legal firm and an NCLT litigant. The firm allegedly demanded Rs 1.5 crore for a favourable order, later reduced to Rs 1 crore. Rs 20 lakh had been paid before the CBI intervened, registering a case and searching involved parties.
title: CBI searches NCLT ex-official’s premises in Rs 1 crore bribery case

description: Posters of UP CM Yogi Adityanath at a rally in Kathmandu caused a stir, highlighting the historical ties between Nepal's former monarchy and Gorakhsh Peeth. Pradeep Bikram Rana, who waved the poster, claimed persecution by Kathmandu authorities, prompting his escape. The Shah dynasty, which aligns with the Gorakhnath sect, maintains traditional ties with the temple, sending offerings annually.
title: Nepal royals' ties to Goraksh Peeth behind Yogi poster in Kathmandu

description: India and Mauritius have upgraded their relationship to an Enhanced Strategic Partnership. Prime Minister Modi emphasized cooperation in defense, maritime security, trade, and development. India will support Mauritius with a new Parliament building and a rupee-denominated line of credit for water pipeline replacement. Both countries reaffirmed commitment to a secure and open Indian Ocean.
title: Sagar to Mahasagar: India upgrades Mauritius ties

description: Karnataka CM Siddaramaiah backed Tamil Nadu's campaign against the population-based delimitation, contrasting with his deputy's cautious stance. A Tamil Nadu delegation proposed a joint action committee, aiming to involve multiple states. The protest revolves around accusations of bias against southern states in the delimitation process. Siddaramaiah condemned actions that weaken democracy and federal principles.
title: Siddaramaiah, DK Shivakumar not on same page as delimitation row escalates

description: Madhya Pradesh's 2025-26 budget sees a 15% increase over the previous year, reaching Rs 4,21,032 crore. Despite no new taxes, several key schemes face cuts, including Ladli Behna Yojana. Major cuts are also seen in allocations for primary and secondary schools, and PM Gram Sadak Yojana.
title: Tiny cut, but Ladli gets lion’s share of MP budget
